The paper proposes a multi-valued extension of logic programs under the stable models semantics, which is a topic related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces an algebraic characterization of the justifications, which is a topic related to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the lattice-based characterization of the algebra, which is a topic related to data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, and cs.LG.
